occurrenceRemarks: Colour off-white. Body short and almost circular outline, legs relatively short. Head with only one pair of appendages, the palps. Proboscis a large forward-pointing cylinder. Most abundant intertidal sea spider, found under boulders. Pictures are unfortunately blur, but we can guess the cylinder shape of the proboscis. So, Tanystylum brevipes is the best guess for the identification. Found on a Burnupena snail, on the rocky shore in Mouille Point, Cape Town.
